## Design Decisions

### Why not modify STSSessionToken in place?
GetSessionToken and AssumeRole serve fundamentally different use-cases:
- GetSessionToken: requires long-term IAM user credentials, adds MFA support
- AssumeRole: works with any credential source including IRSA temporary tokens
Changing the existing generator would be a breaking change for users relying on
the current behaviour (IAM user + optional MFA). A new generator preserves
backwards compatibility.

### Why pass empty role to NewGeneratorSession?
NewGeneratorSession wraps the credentials with stscreds.NewAssumeRoleProvider
when role != "". The provider is lazy — AssumeRole only fires when Retrieve()
is called. If we then called GetSessionToken (as the old generator does), the
SDK uses those assumed-role temporary creds to make the GetSessionToken call,
which AWS rejects. Passing role="" keeps the base credentials plain so we can
call AssumeRole ourselves and return those credentials directly via Retrieve().

### Testability via injectable stsFactoryFunc
The factory function pattern (stsFactoryFunc injected into generate()) lets
tests provide a fakeAssumeRole without any real AWS calls. Consistent with the
pattern used by generators/v1/sts and generators/v1/ecr.

### go.sum copied from generators/v1/sts
The new module has the same transitive dependency graph as the STS generator
(both depend on aws-sdk-go-v2 + auth provider). Copying go.sum avoids needing
internet access for go mod tidy during implementation.

### expiration key is conditional
Static credentials (SecretRef with no role) have CanExpire=false; including a
zero-value expiration would be misleading. The key is only emitted when
creds.CanExpire is true, matching the semantics of the underlying credentials.

## Learnings / Gotchas

- go.work must have a go directive >= the minimum required by all modules.
  After adding a new module run `go work use` to reconcile versions.
- zz_generated.deepcopy.go: manual edits are safe as scaffolding; `make generate`
  will overwrite them with equivalent generated code. Don't rely on the manual
  edit surviving — just run `make generate` early.
- Tests with empty spec + NewGeneratorSession fall through to the SDK default
  credential chain (including IMDS), causing ~5s delay on the "invalid json"
  test case. This is acceptable and matches the existing STS generator's test
  behaviour. Consider using actually-invalid YAML in future tests to avoid this.
